 adulthood. By uncovering the role racial and ethnic differences play early on, we can better understand the sources of inequality in American life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aRacexSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aSocializationzUnited States. 0aTeenagerszUnited StatesxAttitudes. 0aTeenagerszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 4aAfrican American. 4aAsian. 4aLatina. 4aNo jargon. 4aacademic achievement. 4aadolescence. 4aassumptions. 4acase studies. 4acollected data. 4adifferent background. 4adisadvantaged youth. 4aethnicity. 4agap. 4ageneralizations. 4ahigh school. 4alatino. 4alatinx. 4asociology. 4ateens. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aChristerson, Brad, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aEdwards, Korie L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477462840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804774628423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804774628.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles